[{"text": "What do I know", "start": 15.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that would cause me,", "start": 17.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a reticent, Midwestern scientist,", "start": 19.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to get myself arrested", "start": 21.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in front of the White House protesting?", "start": 24.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And what would you do", "start": 27.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "if you knew what I know?", "start": 29.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Let's start with how I got to this point.", "start": 31.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "I was lucky to grow up", "start": 35.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "at a time when it was not difficult", "start": 37.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "for the child of a tenant farmer", "start": 40.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to make his way to the state university.", "start": 42.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And I was really lucky", "start": 44.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to go to the University of Iowa", "start": 47.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "where I could study under Professor James Van Allen", "start": 49.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "who built instruments", "start": 52.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for the first U.S. satellites.", "start": 54.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Professor Van Allen told me", "start": 56.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "about observations of Venus,", "start": 59.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that there was intense microwave radiation.", "start": 62.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Did it mean that Venus had an ionosphere?", "start": 64.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Or was Venus extremely hot?", "start": 67.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The right answer,", "start": 69.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "confirmed by the Soviet Venera spacecraft,", "start": 71.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "was that Venus was very hot --", "start": 76.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "900 degrees Fahrenheit.", "start": 79.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And it was kept hot", "start": 81.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by a thick carbon dioxide atmosphere.", "start": 83.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I was fortunate to join NASA", "start": 86.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and successfully propose", "start": 88.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "an experiment to fly to Venus.", "start": 90.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Our instrument took this image", "start": 92.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of the veil of Venus,", "start": 95.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which turned out to be", "start": 97.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a smog of sulfuric acid.", "start": 99.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But while our instrument was being built,", "start": 102.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I became involved in calculations", "start": 105.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the greenhouse effect", "start": 107.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "here on Earth,", "start": 109.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because we realized", "start": 111.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that our atmospheric composition was changing.", "start": 113.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Eventually, I resigned", "start": 116.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as principal investigator", "start": 118.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on our Venus experiment", "start": 120.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because a planet changing before our eyes", "start": 122.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is more interesting and important.", "start": 125.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Its changes will affect all of humanity.", "start": 127.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The greenhouse effect had been well understood", "start": 130.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for more than a century.", "start": 132.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "British physicist John Tyndall,", "start": 134.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the 1850's,", "start": 136.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "made laboratory measurements", "start": 138.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the infrared radiation,", "start": 140.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which is heat.", "start": 142.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And he showed that gasses such as CO2 absorb heat,", "start": 144.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "thus acting like a blanket", "start": 147.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "warming Earth's surface.", "start": 150.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I worked with other scientists", "start": 152.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to analyze Earth climate observations.", "start": 154.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "In 1981,", "start": 158.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we published an article in Science magazine", "start": 160.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "concluding that observed warming", "start": 163.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of 0.4 degrees Celsius", "start": 165.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the prior century", "start": 167.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "was consistent with the greenhouse effect", "start": 169.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of increasing CO2.", "start": 171.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "That Earth would likely warm in the 1980's,", "start": 173.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and warming would exceed", "start": 176.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the noise level of random weather", "start": 178.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by the end of the century.", "start": 180.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We also said that the 21st century", "start": 182.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "would see shifting climate zones,", "start": 185.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "creation of drought-prone regions", "start": 187.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in North America and Asia,", "start": 189.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "erosion of ice sheets, rising sea levels", "start": 191.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and opening of the fabled Northwest Passage.", "start": 194.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "All of these impacts", "start": 197.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "have since either happened", "start": 199.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or are now well under way.", "start": 201.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "That paper was reported on the front page of the New York Times", "start": 203.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "and led to me testifying to Congress", "start": 207.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the 1980's,", "start": 209.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "testimony in which I emphasized", "start": 211.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that global warming increases both extremes", "start": 214.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of the Earth's water cycle.", "start": 217.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Heatwaves and droughts on one hand,", "start": 220.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "directly from the warming,", "start": 222.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but also, because a warmer atmosphere", "start": 224.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "holds more water vapor", "start": 226.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with its latent energy,", "start": 228.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "rainfall will become", "start": 230.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in more extreme events.", "start": 232.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "There will be stronger storms and greater flooding.", "start": 234.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Global warming hoopla", "start": 237.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "became time-consuming", "start": 240.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and distracted me from doing science --", "start": 242.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "partly because I had complained", "start": 244.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that the White House altered my testimony.", "start": 246.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So I decided to go back", "start": 249.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to strictly doing science", "start": 251.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and leave the communication to others.", "start": 253.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "By 15 years later,", "start": 257.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "evidence of global warming was much stronger.", "start": 260.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Most of the things mentioned in our 1981 paper", "start": 263.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "were facts.", "start": 266.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I had the privilege to speak twice", "start": 268.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to the president's climate task force.", "start": 271.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But energy policies continued to focus", "start": 273.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "on finding more fossil fuels.", "start": 276.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "By then we had two grandchildren,", "start": 279.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Sophie and Connor.", "start": 282.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I decided", "start": 284.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that I did not want them in the future", "start": 286.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to say, \"Opa understood what was happening,", "start": 288.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but he didn't make it clear.\"", "start": 290.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So I decided to give a public talk", "start": 292.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "criticizing the lack of an appropriate energy policy.", "start": 295.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I gave the talk at the University of Iowa in 2004", "start": 298.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and at the 2005 meeting", "start": 301.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of the American Geophysical Union.", "start": 304.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This led to calls", "start": 307.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from the White House to NASA headquarters", "start": 309.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and I was told that I could not give any talks or speak with the media", "start": 311.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "without prior explicit approval", "start": 314.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "by NASA headquarters.", "start": 317.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "After I informed the New York Times", "start": 320.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about these restrictions,", "start": 322.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "NASA was forced to end the censorship.", "start": 324.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But there were consequences.", "start": 327.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I had been using the first line", "start": 329.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the NASA mission statement,", "start": 331.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"To understand and protect the home planet,\"", "start": 333.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to justify my talks.", "start": 336.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Soon the first line of the mission statement", "start": 338.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "was deleted, never to appear again.", "start": 340.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Over the next few years", "start": 344.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I was drawn more and more", "start": 346.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into trying to communicate the urgency", "start": 348.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of a change in energy policies,", "start": 351.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "while still researching the physics of climate change.", "start": 354.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Let me describe the most important conclusion from the physics --", "start": 357.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "first, from Earth's energy balance", "start": 360.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and, second, from Earth's climate history.", "start": 363.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Adding CO2 to the air", "start": 367.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is like throwing another blanket on the bed.", "start": 369.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It reduces Earth's heat radiation to space,", "start": 372.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "so there's a temporary energy imbalance.", "start": 375.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "More energy is coming in", "start": 378.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "than going out,", "start": 380.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "until Earth warms up enough", "start": 382.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to again radiate to space", "start": 384.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as much energy as it absorbs from the Sun.", "start": 386.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So the key quantity", "start": 388.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is Earth's energy imbalance.", "start": 390.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Is there more energy coming in", "start": 393.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "than going out?", "start": 395.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "If so, more warming is in the pipeline.", "start": 397.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It will occur without adding any more greenhouse gasses.", "start": 400.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Now finally,", "start": 404.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we can measure Earth's energy imbalance precisely", "start": 406.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "by measuring the heat content", "start": 410.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in Earth's heat reservoirs.", "start": 412.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The biggest reservoir, the ocean, was the least well measured,", "start": 415.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "until more than 3,000 Argo floats", "start": 418.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "were distributed around the world's ocean.", "start": 421.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "These floats reveal", "start": 424.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that the upper half of the ocean", "start": 426.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is gaining heat at a substantial rate.", "start": 428.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The deep ocean is also gaining heat at a smaller rate,", "start": 431.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and energy is going", "start": 434.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into the net melting of ice all around the planet.", "start": 436.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And the land, to depths of tens of meters,", "start": 439.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is also warming.", "start": 442.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The total energy imbalance now", "start": 444.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is about six-tenths of a watt per square meter.", "start": 447.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "That may not sound like much,", "start": 451.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but when added up over the whole world, it's enormous.", "start": 453.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's about 20 times greater", "start": 456.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "than the rate of energy use by all of humanity.", "start": 459.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's equivalent to exploding", "start": 462.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "400,000 Hiroshima atomic bombs per day", "start": 464.26, "duration": 6.0}, {"text": "365 days per year.", "start": 470.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That's how much extra energy", "start": 473.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Earth is gaining each day.", "start": 475.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This imbalance,", "start": 477.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "if we want to stabilize climate,", "start": 479.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "means that we must reduce CO2", "start": 482.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from 391 ppm, parts per million,", "start": 484.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "back to 350 ppm.", "start": 487.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That is the change needed to restore energy balance", "start": 490.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and prevent further warming.", "start": 493.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Climate change deniers argue", "start": 495.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that the Sun is the main cause of climate change.", "start": 498.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But the measured energy imbalance occurred", "start": 501.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "during the deepest solar minimum in the record,", "start": 504.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "when the Sun's energy reaching Earth was least.", "start": 508.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Yet, there was more energy coming in than going out.", "start": 512.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This shows that the effect of the Sun's variations on climate", "start": 515.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is overwhelmed by the increasing greenhouse gasses,", "start": 518.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "mainly from burning fossil fuels.", "start": 521.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now consider Earth's climate history.", "start": 524.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "These curves for global temperature,", "start": 527.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "atmospheric CO2 and sea level", "start": 529.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "were derived from ocean cores and Antarctic ice cores,", "start": 532.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "from ocean sediments and snowflakes", "start": 535.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that piled up year after year", "start": 537.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "over 800,000 years", "start": 540.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "forming a two-mile thick ice sheet.", "start": 542.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "As you see, there's a high correlation", "start": 544.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "between temperature, CO2 and sea level.", "start": 547.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Careful examination shows", "start": 550.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that the temperature changes", "start": 552.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "slightly lead the CO2 changes", "start": 554.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by a few centuries.", "start": 556.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Climate change deniers like to use this fact", "start": 559.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to confuse and trick the public", "start": 562.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "by saying, \"Look, the temperature causes CO2 to change,", "start": 565.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "not vice versa.\"", "start": 568.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But that lag", "start": 570.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is exactly what is expected.", "start": 572.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Small changes in Earth's orbit", "start": 575.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that occur over tens to hundreds of thousands of years", "start": 578.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "alter the distribution", "start": 581.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of sunlight on Earth.", "start": 583.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "When there is more sunlight", "start": 585.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "at high latitudes in summer, ice sheets melt.", "start": 587.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Shrinking ice sheets", "start": 590.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "make the planet darker,", "start": 592.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "so it absorbs more sunlight", "start": 594.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and becomes warmer.", "start": 596.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "A warmer ocean releases CO2,", "start": 598.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "just as a warm Coca-Cola does.", "start": 600.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And more CO2 causes more warming.", "start": 603.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So CO2, methane, and ice sheets", "start": 606.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "were feedbacks", "start": 609.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that amplified global temperature change", "start": 611.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "causing these ancient climate oscillations to be huge,", "start": 614.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "even though the climate change was initiated", "start": 617.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "by a very weak forcing.", "start": 620.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The important point", "start": 622.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is that these same amplifying feedbacks", "start": 624.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "will occur today.", "start": 626.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The physics does not change.", "start": 628.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "As Earth warms,", "start": 630.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "now because of extra CO2 we put in the atmosphere,", "start": 632.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "ice will melt,", "start": 635.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and CO2 and methane will be released", "start": 637.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by warming ocean and melting permafrost.", "start": 639.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "While we can't say exactly how fast", "start": 642.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "these amplifying feedbacks will occur,", "start": 645.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "it is certain they will occur,", "start": 648.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "unless we stop the warming.", "start": 651.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "There is evidence", "start": 653.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that feedbacks are already beginning.", "start": 655.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Precise measurements", "start": 658.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by GRACE, the gravity satellite,", "start": 660.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "reveal that both Greenland and Antarctica", "start": 662.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "are now losing mass,", "start": 665.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "several hundred cubic kilometers per year.", "start": 667.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And the rate has accelerated", "start": 670.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "since the measurements began", "start": 672.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "nine years ago.", "start": 674.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Methane is also beginning", "start": 676.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to escape from the permafrost.", "start": 678.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "What sea level rise", "start": 681.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "can we look forward to?", "start": 683.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The last time CO2 was 390 ppm,", "start": 685.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "today's value,", "start": 688.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "sea level was higher", "start": 690.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by at least 15 meters, 50 feet.", "start": 692.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Where you are sitting now", "start": 695.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "would be under water.", "start": 697.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Most estimates are that, this century,", "start": 699.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "we will get at least one meter.", "start": 702.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I think it will be more", "start": 704.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "if we keep burning fossil fuels,", "start": 706.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "perhaps even five meters, which is 18 feet,", "start": 708.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "this century or shortly thereafter.", "start": 711.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The important point", "start": 714.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is that we will have started a process", "start": 716.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that is out of humanity's control.", "start": 719.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Ice sheets would continue to disintegrate for centuries.", "start": 722.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "There would be no stable shoreline.", "start": 725.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The economic consequences are almost unthinkable.", "start": 727.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Hundreds of New Orleans-like devastations", "start": 730.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "around the world.", "start": 734.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What may be more reprehensible,", "start": 736.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "if climate denial continues,", "start": 738.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is extermination of species.", "start": 740.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The monarch butterfly", "start": 742.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "could be one of the 20 to 50 percent of all species", "start": 744.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "that the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change estimates", "start": 749.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "will be ticketed for extinction", "start": 752.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by the end of the century", "start": 754.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "if we stay on business-as-usual fossil fuel use.", "start": 756.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Global warming is already affecting people.", "start": 760.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The Texas, Oklahoma, Mexico", "start": 763.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "heatwave and drought last year,", "start": 765.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Moscow the year before", "start": 768.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and Europe in 2003,", "start": 770.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "were all exceptional events,", "start": 772.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "more than three standard deviations outside the norm.", "start": 775.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Fifty years ago,", "start": 779.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "such anomalies", "start": 781.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "covered only two- to three-tenths", "start": 783.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of one percent of the land area.", "start": 785.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "In recent years,", "start": 787.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because of global warming,", "start": 789.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they now cover about 10 percent --", "start": 791.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "an increase by a factor of 25 to 50.", "start": 793.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So we can say with a high degree of confidence", "start": 796.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that the severe Texas and Moscow heatwaves", "start": 799.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "were not natural;", "start": 801.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they were caused by global warming.", "start": 803.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "An important impact,", "start": 806.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "if global warming continues,", "start": 808.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "will be on the breadbasket of our nation and the world,", "start": 810.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the Midwest and Great Plains,", "start": 813.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which are expected to become prone to extreme droughts,", "start": 815.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "worse than the Dust Bowl,", "start": 818.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "within just a few decades,", "start": 820.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "if we let global warming continue.", "start": 822.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "How did I get dragged deeper and deeper", "start": 826.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "into an attempt to communicate,", "start": 829.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "giving talks in 10 countries, getting arrested,", "start": 831.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "burning up the vacation time", "start": 834.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that I had accumulated over 30 years?", "start": 836.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "More grandchildren helped me along.", "start": 840.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Jake is a super-positive,", "start": 843.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "enthusiastic boy.", "start": 845.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Here at age two and a half years,", "start": 848.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "he thinks he can protect", "start": 850.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "his two and a half-day-old little sister.", "start": 852.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It would be immoral", "start": 855.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to leave these young people", "start": 857.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with a climate system", "start": 859.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "spiraling out of control.", "start": 861.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Now the tragedy about climate change", "start": 863.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is that we can solve it", "start": 866.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with a simple, honest approach", "start": 868.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of a gradually rising carbon fee", "start": 870.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "collected from fossil fuel companies", "start": 873.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and distributed 100 percent electronically", "start": 875.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "every month to all legal residents", "start": 879.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on a per capita basis,", "start": 881.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with the government not keeping one dime.", "start": 883.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Most people would get more in the monthly dividend", "start": 887.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "than they'd pay in increased prices.", "start": 890.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This fee and dividend", "start": 892.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "would stimulate the economy", "start": 894.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and innovations,", "start": 896.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "creating millions of jobs.", "start": 898.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It is the principal requirement", "start": 900.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for moving us rapidly", "start": 902.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to a clean energy future.", "start": 905.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Several top economists", "start": 907.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are coauthors on this proposition.", "start": 909.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Jim DiPeso of Republicans for Environmental Protection", "start": 912.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "describes it thusly:", "start": 915.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"Transparent. Market-based.", "start": 917.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Does not enlarge government.", "start": 919.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Leaves energy decisions to individual choices.", "start": 921.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Sounds like a conservative climate plan.\"", "start": 924.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "But instead of placing a rising fee on carbon emissions", "start": 928.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "to make fossil fuels pay", "start": 932.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "their true cost to society,", "start": 935.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "our governments are forcing the public", "start": 937.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to subsidize fossil fuels", "start": 940.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "by 400 to 500 billion dollars", "start": 943.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "per year worldwide,", "start": 946.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "thus encouraging extraction of every fossil fuel --", "start": 948.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "mountaintop removal,", "start": 951.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "longwall mining, fracking,", "start": 953.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "tar sands, tar shale,", "start": 955.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "deep ocean Arctic drilling.", "start": 957.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This path, if continued,", "start": 960.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "guarantees that we will pass tipping points", "start": 962.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "leading to ice sheet disintegration", "start": 965.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that will accelerate out of control of future generations.", "start": 967.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "A large fraction of species", "start": 971.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "will be committed to extinction.", "start": 973.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And increasing intensity of droughts and floods", "start": 975.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "will severely impact breadbaskets of the world,", "start": 977.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "causing massive famines", "start": 980.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and economic decline.", "start": 982.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Imagine a giant asteroid", "start": 986.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "on a direct collision course with Earth.", "start": 989.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "That is the equivalent", "start": 993.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of what we face now.", "start": 995.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Yet, we dither,", "start": 997.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "taking no action", "start": 999.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to divert the asteroid,", "start": 1001.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "even though the longer we wait,", "start": 1003.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the more difficult and expensive it becomes.", "start": 1005.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "If we had started in 2005,", "start": 1009.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it would have required emission reductions of three percent per year", "start": 1011.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to restore planetary energy balance", "start": 1014.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and stabilize climate this century.", "start": 1017.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "If we start next year,", "start": 1020.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it is six percent per year.", "start": 1022.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "If we wait 10 years, it is 15 percent per year --", "start": 1024.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "extremely difficult and expensive,", "start": 1027.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "perhaps impossible.", "start": 1029.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But we aren't even starting.", "start": 1032.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So now you know what I know", "start": 1034.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that is moving me to sound this alarm.", "start": 1037.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Clearly, I haven't gotten this message across.", "start": 1040.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The science is clear.", "start": 1043.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I need your help", "start": 1046.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to communicate the gravity and the urgency", "start": 1048.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of this situation", "start": 1050.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and its solutions", "start": 1052.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "more effectively.", "start": 1054.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We owe it to our children and grandchildren.", "start": 1056.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 1058.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 1060.26, "duration": 5.0}]